quran[12]{c,v,t}:
  16,15,"He has set up on the earth firm mountains, lest it shake under you, and rivers and tracks, so that you may find your way"
  16,16,and He has set up other landmarks. By these and by the stars people set their course
  16,17,"Is He, then, who creates like him who does not create? Will you not, then, take heed"
  16,18,"If you tried to count God's blessings, you would never be able to number them. God is ever forgiving and most merciful"
  16,19,God knows all that you conceal and all that you reveal
  16,20,Those you call on besides God cannot create anything. They are themselves created
  16,21,"They are dead, not living; nor do they know when they will be raised to life"
  16,22,"Your God is the One God. As for those who do not believe in the Hereafter, their hearts refuse to admit the truth and they are arrogant"
  16,23,God surely knows what they conceal and what they reveal. He does not love the arrogant
  16,24,"When they are asked, \"What is it that your Lord has sent down?\" they say, \"Stories of the ancients"
  16,25,Let them bear all their own burdens on Resurrection Day as well as some of the burdens of those whom they lead astray without any knowledge. How evil the load with which they shall be burdened
  16,26,"Those who went before them also plotted. But God struck at the foundations of their building, and the roof fell down upon them from above. The punishment came upon them from where they did not expect"